                        <additions>
                          <list>
                          <item xml:id="a1">
                            <desc>List of indulgences. Note describing the rewards in the future life for good deeds performed by Christians. Incipit: ስምዑ፡ ዘወሀበ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ተስፋ፡ ለምእመናን፡ ፴፻፼በምሥራቅ፡ ወበምዕራብ፡ በደቡብ፡ ወበስሜን፡ ከመዝ፡ ይከውን፡ ፍሬሁ፡ ዘይጼሊ፡ በቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ፷፼፡ ለ፩፡ ሰጊድ፡ ፍሬሁ፡. The note is written in a fine hand contemporary with that of the main text. The conclusion is partly illegible due to faded ink</desc>
                            <locus target="#92r">Fol. 92r</locus>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="a2">
                            <desc>Mǝʿǝraf śalast (II part). Chant taken from the Məʿraf (The Common of the Office), 2nd part, śäläst. Incipit: ስምዓኒ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ጸሎትየ፡ ሃሌ፡ ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ወይብጻሕ፡ ቅድሜከ፡ ገዓርየ፡ ሃሌ፡ ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ወአትሜጥ፡ ገጸከ፡ እምኔየ፡ አእርፎሙ፡ ነፍሰ፡ እለ፡ ኖሙ፡ በእደ፡ ኄራን፡. The note is written in the same hand as note 1. It is preceded and followed by two notes carefully erased</desc>
                            <locus target="#92v">Fol. 92v</locus>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="a3">
                            <desc>Short note written in dark red ink in a recent hand. The full text is the following: ጸሎተ፡ ባህታዊ፡ ሶበ፡ ይቴከዝ፡ ስእለቶ፡ ቅድመ፡ እግዚአብሔር።, “Prayer of the hermit when he is concerned about his request before God”. It presumably refers to Ps 101, which begins immediately below the note</desc>
                            <locus target="#93r">Fol. 93r</locus>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="a4">
                            <desc type="Record">Note describing the feast of Mary’s Ascension into heaven (16 Näḥase). Incipit: ዮም፡ ፍስሀ፡ ኮነ፡ በእ[ን]ተ፡ ፍልሰታ፡ ለማርያም፡ በሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፡ እምድር፡ እስከ፡ አርያም፡ ዕፁብ፡ ግብር፡ ተገብረ፡ ለባሕቲታ፡ አማን፡ መንክር፡ ስብሐተ፡ ፍልሰታ።. The note is written in a fine recent hand.</desc>
                            <locus target="#93r">Fol. 93r</locus>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e1">
                            <locus target="#179r">Fol. 179r</locus>
                            <p>Pen trials.</p>
                          </item>
                        </list>
                        </additions>

                        <bindingDesc>
                          <binding contemporary="true" xml:id="binding">
                            <decoNote xml:id="b1">The book is sewn on four sewing stations (two pairs) linked to wooden boards with a leather half cover.</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Cover">
                              The book has half cover of brown-reddish leather decorated with blind tooled motifs. <term key="singleStraightLine" ana="#singleStraightLine">Single straight lines</term> divide the space in squares where they cross, forming a "X".
                              On the right board, a <term key="singleCircle" ana="#singleCircle">single circle</term> is placed at the intersections.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="Endbands" color="brown black">
                              The codex has <term key="slitBraid" ana="#slitBraid">slit-braid</term>endbands sewn to the text block with a thread of animal origin.
                              Not every quire has tiedowns. The quires that don't have tiedowns, don't have additional holes even.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b7">
                              The sewing is a chain-stitch on four sewing stations (two pairs). The sewing pattern is a variation of the <term key="patternA3" ana="#patternA3">pattern A3</term> by Bozzacchi.
                              Along the fold of the first quire, for each pair of sewing station there is one long stitch without knots. In the second quire there are two long stitches.
                              The thread used for the sewing is of <term key="animalThread" ana="#animalThread">animal origin</term>.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b10" type="Other">
                              Parchment <term key="guard" ana="#guard">guards</term> are found in <locus target="#q1 #q2 #q23">quires: 1, 2 and 23</locus>.
                            </decoNote>
                          </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
